    }), "\n", _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "This wasn’t just any car, but a canvas that traversed roads and hearts alike, painted with motifs of the Ndebele tribe. With this, Esther Mahlangu not only broke the boundaries of the art world but also shattered the glass ceiling, being the first non-Western person and the first female to design a BMW Art Car. This vibrant automobile was later exhibited at the National Museum of Women in the Arts in Washington, DC, in 1994, and at the British Museum, London in 2017, further propelling Mahlangu’s name into the annals of art history."
